1775770605536669	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErAw		item.create	bn-3en5	{"description":"When rebasing a workspace that contains an empty commit (git commit --allow-empty), the cherry-pick fails (expected) but the warning message has no reason after the colon:\n\n  Warning: commit after cherry-pick failed for a0cc7578dff3: \n\nThe trailing empty string after the colon looks like a truncated message. Should either:\n1. Include a reason like 'empty commit (no changes to apply)' \n2. Skip empty commits silently with an info message\n3. Use --allow-empty during cherry-pick\n\nNot a data loss issue — the rebase completes and the workspace is updated correctly. Cosmetic only.","kind":"task","title":"sync --rebase: empty warning message when cherry-picking empty commits"}	blake3:82L9Ug7F9Osd7SEDV5cczBv06SbhknsOvocGrHMrU88
